In `Services/FileService.cs`, the private static `CopyDirectory(string source, string destination)` helper recurses with no depth bound. A deeply nested (or, on buggy filesystems, self-referential) directory structure could cause a stack overflow. Add a max-depth bound: change the signature to `CopyDirectory(string source, string destination, int depth)` and add a new public-internal overload OR have the public `Copy` method pass an initial depth of 0 and the recursive call pass `depth + 1`. Define a `private const int MaxCopyDepth = 32;` constant. When `depth >= MaxCopyDepth`, throw `new IOException("Directory copy depth limit exceeded (possible cycle)")`. Update the docstring to mention the depth limit. Do NOT change the public `Copy(CopyRequest)` signature. The lazy `Root` accessor added by task-16 must be used in place of the previous `_root` field. Verification: `dotnet test TestProject.Tests/TestProject.Tests.csproj` — all `Copy_*` tests still pass; the test-writing phase may add a test that constructs a deep directory structure (depth > 32) and asserts an IOException is thrown.

